headlines.description: Akwasi Yeboah had his third double-double of the season, UC Iroegbu and Jakub Petras scored 16 points apiece and Stony Brook beat UMass Lowell 81-68 on Thursday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Yeboah's double-double helps Stony Brook beat UMass Lowell

headlines.description: Sam McDaniel drilled a trey in the final seconds of overtime and Louisiana-Monroe slipped past Georgia Southern 66-64 in Sun Belt Conference play on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDaniel's late 3 helps Louisiana-Monroe get 66-64 OT win

headlines.description: Grant Benzinger and Jaylon Hall each hit back-to-back 3-pointers as Wright State made up an 11-point gap in less than two minutes and then held off an upset-minded Green bay 68-64 Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrage of 3s helps Wright State to 68-64 win over Green Bay

headlines.description: Giddy Potts made six 3-pointers and finished with 22 points to help Middle Tennessee cruise to a 94-75 victory over Rice on Thursday night to its sixth straight win.
Jermaine Marrow and Kalin Fisher scored 19 points apiece and combined to hit 7 of 12 from 3-point range to help Hampton beat Howard 95-81 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marrow, Fisher score 19 apiece, Hampton beats Howard 95-81

headlines.description: Jordan Giles and Xavier Bishop each scored 18 points and Missouri-Kansas City upended Seattle 74-67 Thursday night, snapping the Redhawks' three-game win streak and securing a season sweep.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giles, Bishop score 18 each, help UMKC sweep Seattle 74-67

headlines.description: Dikembe Dixson finished with 22 points, Marcus Ottey scored 19 and the pair combined to make 16 of 17 free throws to lead Illinois-Chicago to a 100-75 victory over Youngstown State on Thursday night for its seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dixson, Ottey lead UIC past Youngstown State 100-75

headlines.description: Kenneth Ogbe and Conner Toolson each scored 18 points with four 3-pointers and Utah Valley never trailed in its 97-57 defeat of Chicago State on Thursday night.
Frankie Ferrari had 13 points on 4-of-5 shooting and Nate Renfro scored 12 points to help San Francisco hold on for a 65-63 win over Portland on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Francisco holds off Portland for 65-63 win

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
